    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-17T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-17T14:00:00-05:00" n="589"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/9–1751: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States</hi> (<hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss target="#t_GATT1" type="from">GATT</gloss>
                    </hi>) <hi rend="italic">Delegation to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d589fn1">For the composition of the U.S. Delegation to the
                        Sixth Session of the Contracting Parties of the General Agreement on Tariffs
                        and Trade which convened at Geneva on September 17, 1951, see Department of
                        State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, October 1, 1951, p. 553. The
                        Delegation Chairman was Willard L. Thorp, Assistant Secretary of State for
                        Economic Affairs, and the Vice Chairman was John M. Leddy, Acting Director,
                        Office of Economic Defense and Trade Policy. Files of the U.S. Delegation
                        are in the <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> Files, Lot 63 D 134, Box
                        268 (FRC Accession 65A987) and Lot 66 D 209, Box 454 (FRC Accession
                        71A6682).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-17T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 17, 1951—8 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tagg1">Tagg</gloss> 7. At plenary <gloss target="#t_GATT1"
                        >GATT</gloss> session today<note n="2" xml:id="d589fn2">The Summary Records
                        of the Sixth Session are in <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> Files, Lot
                        63 D 134, Box 268. There were 27 plenary meetings, September 17–October 27,
                        1951.</note> Czech delegate reserved right place two additional items on
                    agenda if diplomatic representations in Wash do not bring satisfactory replies.
                    First complaint related to general US action in refusing all export licenses for
                    export to Czech. Second item refers to refusal of specific export licenses for
                    Czech goods sent to US and rejected by US customers. Czech seek to have these
                    goods returned to Czech. Claim some of these latter goods not permitted be
                    re-exported.</p>
                <p>Pls send soonest available background and what steps will be taken.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept <gloss target="#t_Tagg1">Tagg</gloss> 7, rptd info Praha 1.</p>
            </div>
